race.comment: LITTLE MASTER (1) flew the lids from the middle with an impressive turn of foot, going on to clock 19.72 when a one length winner over 350m at this track. The form out of last race has been strong. Form reads well for this. RATTLIN' BONES (7) flew the lids off the inside with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow fourth (19.51) over 350m at this track. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Should play a prominent role. JAICOS (2) was an impressive winner last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 3.5 lengths (22.17) at Shepparton. Harder here but expected to feature again. ZINZAN SAMMY (3) warrants respect following a recent placing.
